    "buildCommand": null,
    "testCommand": "git commit --no-gpg-sign -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\ntest: add real-source test infrastructure and expand coverage\n\n## Test infrastructure\n\n- Add `tests/setup/load-source.js`: vm.Script loader that evaluates source\n  files via runInThisContext so v8 attributes coverage to the real file\n  instead of a mock module.\n- Add `tests/unit/content/_setup.js`: shared helper that builds the full\n  content-script DOM, resets the IIFE guard (`window.__mdSnInitialized`),\n  loads lib + content.js, and returns the `__mdSn_content` API handle.\n- Add `tests/unit/popup/_setup.js`: shared helper that builds the full\n  popup DOM (tabs, modals, settings panel, snippet/alert lists), loads lib\n  + popup.js, and returns the `__mdSn_popup` API handle.\n\n## Debug-export footers (source files)\n\nAdd `globalThis.__mdSn_*` export blocks to the three non-module source\nfiles so tests can access internal functions after real-source loading:\n- `background/background.js` → `__mdSn_background`\n- `content/content.js`       → `__mdSn_content`\n- `popup/popup.js`           → `__mdSn_popup`\n\n## New test files (content script)\n\n- `tests/unit/content/conversion-flow.test.js`: convertTextarea,\n  restoreMarkdown, undo stack, event dispatch, and notification rendering.\n- `tests/unit/content/dom-observer.test.js`: MutationObserver-based\n  enhanceJournalFields and observeDOM behaviour.\n- `tests/unit/content/picker-dropdowns.test.js`: alert picker and snippet\n  picker insertion flows.\n- `tests/unit/content/preview-modal.test.js`: openPreviewModal rendering,\n  sanitizeHtml XSS stripping, and modal close logic.\n\n## New test files (popup)\n\n- `tests/unit/popup/debug.test.js`: smoke-tests that the `__mdSn_popup`\n  debug export is populated after real-source load.\n\n## Refactored existing tests to use real-source loading\n\n- `tests/unit/background/background.test.js`: replaced mock-only approach\n  with `loadSource`; captures listener callbacks from `mock.calls` after\n  the module loads (`onInstalled`, `onStartup`, `onClicked`, `onMessage`,\n  `onChanged`).\n- `tests/unit/popup/popup.test.js`: replaced inline DOM + mock setup with\n  `setupPopup()` helper; tests now exercise the real popup code paths.\n- `tests/unit/popup/alert-management.test.js`: same migration; tests now\n  hit real alert CRUD, validation, import/export, and storage sync logic.\n\n## Chrome API mock additions\n\nAdd three previously-missing entries to `tests/mocks/chrome-api.js` that\nare required by the real source code:\n- `chrome.runtime.onStartup` with `addListener` stub\n- `chrome.contextMenus.removeAll` (calls callback immediately)\n- `chrome.storage.onChanged` with `addListener` stub\n\n## Coverage config\n\nExclude `docs/**` from vitest coverage so the docs copy of the library\ndoes not drag overall line/function/branch percentages below threshold.\n\n## CLAUDE.md\n\nDocument the real-source loading pattern, `loadSource` / `setupContent` /\n`setupPopup` helpers, fake-timer ordering constraint, lib→globalThis mirror\nstep, IIFE guard reset, and the `__mdSn_*` debug-export contract.\nEOF\n)\"",
